race.comment: SPICY WINGS (9) hasn't been close up since his Maiden win three runs back, the latest over 1550m at Murwillumbah. Has good early toe and has weight relief. In the right yard and will be hard to roll. OCEAN DIVA (8) presents third-up and will appreciate the step up in trip. Has an awkward barrier but Morgan rides. Should be around the mark. They don't come much more consistent than IN THE FINE PRINT (4) who has finished ut of the money just once in eight starts this campaign. Has thrived since arriving in the Northern Rivers region. MAMMOTH MOUNTAIN (14) faded at Inverell last start. Had strung together three straight placings prior to that.
